00:03:11.290 --> 00:03:13.460
And these are basically-- and
it's pretty obvious, right?

00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:17.120
It's dialogues that appear that
say loading, or saving,

00:03:17.120 --> 00:03:18.790
or sending, or whatever.

00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:22.500
And sometimes you can't even
press Back to cancel.

00:03:22.500 --> 00:03:24.500
If you have poor network
connectivity, there's just no

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:26.770
way out, except for
pressing Hoe.

00:03:26.770 --> 00:03:30.660
And it's one of the easiest ways
to tick off your users.

00:03:30.660 --> 00:03:33.980
Especially those that, like
I said, aren't in a good

00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:35.700
connectivity setting.

00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:38.230
Or those that simply
are very quickly.

00:03:38.230 --> 00:03:40.460
They're trying to do a bunch
of things at once.

00:03:40.460 --> 00:03:42.940
The other thing I'll quickly
