00:03:42.940 --> 00:03:45.780
peeves is when you throw up
a loading dialogue when

00:03:45.780 --> 00:03:47.870
switching tabs.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:49.680
Because basically, you
switch to tab.

00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:51.830
Maybe you accidentally
chose that tab.

00:03:51.830 --> 00:03:54.840
And now you have to wait for
that tab to load to switch to

00:03:54.840 --> 00:03:55.820
something else.

00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:59.790
So the solution to this is
really to try to use inline

00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:03.870
loading spinners instead, like
in this little graphic here.

00:04:03.870 --> 00:04:07.630
Or better yet, just try to load
data in the background

00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:10.200
where possible, so that you
can generally just avoid

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:12.120
[? showing ?] loading
spinners.

