00:07:08.945 --> 00:07:09.370
ROMAN NURIK: Yep.

00:07:09.370 --> 00:07:11.870
So number eight,
visual design.

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:15.040
I think this was the one
I'll talk about.

00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:19.890
So in general, design does not
mean playing with Photoshop

00:07:19.890 --> 00:07:22.740
until you use all
of the effects.

00:07:22.740 --> 00:07:26.600
Until you use all of the layer
effects, like here on the

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:28.920
left, with the drop shadows
and all of that.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:32.550
There are a couple of concepts
here going on.

00:07:32.550 --> 00:07:35.640
Basically, when you think about
visual design for your

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:39.970
app, focus really on content,
rather than Chrome.

00:07:39.970 --> 00:07:42.470
Users really aren't installing
your app just to see the

00:07:42.470 --> 00:07:46.930
pretty buttons, and the
pretty top bars, and

00:07:46.930 --> 00:07:48.580
all these fancy things.

00:07:48.580 --> 00:07:50.790
They're really installing your
app, probably because they

00:07:50.790 --> 00:07:53.860
care about the content or the
functionality that you offer.

00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:55.430
So really make that shine.

00:07:55.430 --> 00:07:58.200
If you're going to dedicate any
sort of visual attention

00:07:58.200 --> 00:08:01.100
or visual resources to anything,
it should really be

00:08:01.100 --> 00:08:02.590
the content.

00:08:02.590 --> 00:08:05.370
Additionally, a couple of other
things in the realm of

00:08:05.370 --> 00:08:07.300
visual styling for your app.

00:08:07.300 --> 00:08:08.560
Try to be consistent.

00:08:08.560 --> 00:08:12.820
All too often, we see apps
that have three or four

00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:15.180
different button styles,
or check

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:16.400
box styles, or something.

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:19.310
And they're kind of mixing
and matching.

00:08:19.310 --> 00:08:22.950
And generally, that can be the
result of too many people, too

00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:24.210
many cooks in the kitchen.

00:08:24.210 --> 00:08:26.670
Too many people working
on the same app.

00:08:26.670 --> 00:08:29.860
So where possible, try to
introduce consistency, using

00:08:29.860 --> 00:08:33.340
things like Android's styles
and themes, framework, to

00:08:33.340 --> 00:08:34.780
basically make it
really simple.

00:08:34.780 --> 00:08:38.070
To have consistent style
across your app.

00:08:38.070 --> 00:08:42.990
And the last thing in the realm
of visual design is poor

00:08:42.990 --> 00:08:44.150
attention to detail.

00:08:44.150 --> 00:08:46.885
So it's not only about getting
the high level things right.

00:08:46.885 --> 00:08:51.060
Like getting the right color
and getting the right basic

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:51.930
theme down.

00:08:51.930 --> 00:08:54.670
It's really about attention to
details, with respect to

00:08:54.670 --> 00:08:55.400
typography.

00:08:55.400 --> 00:08:59.990
Making sure you're using the
right typographic palette.

00:08:59.990 --> 00:09:01.520
Also, with respect to metrics.

00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:03.170
That's one of the biggest things
that people do wrong

00:09:03.170 --> 00:09:04.000
that we see.

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.060
Is developers don't use
the right spacing.

00:09:08.060 --> 00:09:09.720
So there's two little space.

00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:13.200
Or there's too much space
around an element.

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:16.100
Or too small margins
around the sides.

00:09:16.100 --> 00:09:18.980
And things like that can really
break the concept of

00:09:18.980 --> 00:09:22.020
alignment and visual balance
within your app.

00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:23.520
So definitely focus
on these things.

00:09:23.520 --> 00:09:25.720
And I think certainly, we've
covered most of these on

00:09:25.720 --> 00:09:28.700
"Android Design in Action"
in episodes past.

00:09:28.700 --> 00:09:30.370
But definitely, this is
one of the things you

00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:33.130
should focus on.

00:09:33.130 --> 00:09:35.580
Anything else before
I move on?

