00:09:52.510 --> 00:09:56.130
So the first point I want to
make about this is the menu

00:09:56.130 --> 00:09:58.680
button of shame, or the
legacy menu button.

00:09:58.680 --> 00:10:01.630
It's kind of very
little excuse.

00:10:01.630 --> 00:10:04.690
All of these [INAUDIBLE] we've
got on the slide here

00:10:04.690 --> 00:10:08.010
generally point towards the fact
that you've not updating

00:10:08.010 --> 00:10:10.400
your application to move
with the latest.

00:10:10.400 --> 00:10:12.500
It's one thing to look at the
platform distribution stats

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:16.160
and say, hey, somebody uses
it on all their devices.

00:10:16.160 --> 00:10:19.955
But that's not really being fair
to the users who are on

00:10:19.955 --> 00:10:22.420
your devices, or have these
shiny, new devices.

00:10:22.420 --> 00:10:24.370
Probably the people who are
downloading and installing

00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:27.210
your application more often.

00:10:27.210 --> 00:10:31.900
So we really think you need to
be looking at, maybe not the

00:10:31.900 --> 00:10:32.980
blazing latest release.

00:10:32.980 --> 00:10:36.230
But here we said you should be
targeting at least API 16,

00:10:36.230 --> 00:10:37.945
which is the first Jellybean
release,

00:10:37.945 --> 00:10:39.020
which came out at what?

00:10:39.020 --> 00:10:40.090
Google I/O last year?

00:10:40.090 --> 00:10:41.622
So over a year old.

00:10:41.622 --> 00:10:45.380
If you're not targeting that
newer version, you're probably

00:10:45.380 --> 00:10:48.540
missing out on some new
functionality, as well as

00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:50.160
probably degrading some
of the functionality.

00:10:50.160 --> 00:10:53.370
Because some of the shims
that their system

00:10:53.370 --> 00:10:54.340
has to put in place.

00:10:54.340 --> 00:10:56.500
Like the [INAUDIBLE] button.

00:10:56.500 --> 00:10:58.980
So if you're below 14, I think
you've got a real big problem.

00:10:58.980 --> 00:11:01.350
Because you're going to get
this legacy menu emulator

00:11:01.350 --> 00:11:02.790
button, button of shame.

00:11:02.790 --> 00:11:03.440
It could look terrible.

00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:06.790
Especially on devices like the
HT1, where it puts up this big

00:11:06.790 --> 00:11:07.980
bar across the bottom
of your application.

00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:12.550
And really ruins all the time
and attention I hope you spent

00:11:12.550 --> 00:11:13.820
on the rest of the design.

00:11:13.820 --> 00:11:16.720
So really think about that.

00:11:16.720 --> 00:11:20.210
And the other thing is
not picking up on the

00:11:20.210 --> 00:11:21.590
modern look and feel.

00:11:21.590 --> 00:11:25.520
So for example, if I'm using
an application, and it has

00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:28.730
some kind of gingerbread
era and stying.

00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:30.180
For example, it might
look kind of hollow.

00:11:30.180 --> 00:11:31.282
But then you touch something,
and you

00:11:31.282 --> 00:11:32.980
get that orange highlight.

00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:37.090
Or you scroll and you get that
legacy, rounded scroll bar.

00:11:37.090 --> 00:11:38.210
Maybe you're familiar
with that.

00:11:38.210 --> 00:11:40.730
That really breaks the
experiences for me.

00:11:40.730 --> 00:11:42.940
Suddenly it's just like, wow,
that was unexpected.

00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:43.980
What's going on there?

00:11:43.980 --> 00:11:47.450
So wherever possible, you want
to be using the latest and

00:11:47.450 --> 00:11:48.260
greatest styles.

00:11:48.260 --> 00:11:51.960
And building on top of them,
using them as your foundation.

00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:54.410
I think when I often see this
is with spinners as well.

00:11:54.410 --> 00:11:55.930
So you'll be using
an application.

00:11:55.930 --> 00:11:59.180
And they set a style on the an

00:11:59.180 --> 00:12:00.190
indeterminate progress spinner.

00:12:00.190 --> 00:12:02.050
Often set the style
to indeterminate.

00:12:02.050 --> 00:12:05.330
And they haven't used the
appropriate theme default

00:12:05.330 --> 00:12:06.140
syntax for it.

00:12:06.140 --> 00:12:09.050
So you get style spinner.

00:12:09.050 --> 00:12:12.150
And it just looks completely
gross and out of place.

00:12:12.150 --> 00:12:13.790
ROMAN NURIK: The other problem
with the loading spinner is

00:12:13.790 --> 00:12:16.530
that the gingerbread era one
used frame animation.

00:12:16.530 --> 00:12:18.730
So there are basically
8 frames, like

00:12:18.730 --> 00:12:19.990
dik-dik-dik-dik-dik and so on.

00:12:19.990 --> 00:12:22.030
And the hollow spinner
is actually

00:12:22.030 --> 00:12:23.660
using a tween animation.

00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:25.620
So it's a much smoother
rotation.

00:12:25.620 --> 00:12:27.580
You actually see
each individual

00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:28.890
frame as it gets rendered.

00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:31.740
Well, not each individual frame,
but each point around

00:12:31.740 --> 00:12:32.230
the circle.

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:35.270
So it's much, much better
to use the hollow style

00:12:35.270 --> 00:12:37.470
interminable loading spinners.

00:12:37.470 --> 00:12:40.030
NICK BUTCHER: Yeah, so I guess
the takeaway from this, what

00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:42.790
we're trying to say here, is use
the latest and greatest.

00:12:42.790 --> 00:12:46.130
And build on top of it.

00:12:46.130 --> 00:12:46.750
ROMAN NURIK: Excellent.

00:12:46.750 --> 00:12:48.000
Moving on?

00:12:49.970 --> 00:12:50.750
OK.

00:12:50.750 --> 00:12:51.830
Polluted Android.

00:12:51.830 --> 00:12:52.640
Who is going to talk
about that?

00:12:52.640 --> 00:12:53.030
NICK BUTCHER: I think
that's me again.

00:12:53.030 --> 00:12:56.300
So there's a page on the design

00:12:56.300 --> 00:12:57.610
guide called Pure Android.

00:12:57.610 --> 00:12:59.320
And it is what it sounds like.

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:00.520
It's talking about don't borrow

00:13:00.520 --> 00:13:02.690
metaphors from other platforms.

00:13:02.690 --> 00:13:06.920
Don't use iconography or other
such from other platforms.

00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:09.440
If you're building an Android
experience for your Android

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:12.930
users, then build an
Android experience.

00:13:12.930 --> 00:13:15.670
I think we did a whole show
about branding inconsistency.

00:13:15.670 --> 00:13:18.330
Whether you should be
consistent with--

00:13:18.330 --> 00:13:18.680
and what that means.

00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:20.560
What you should be consistent
with if you're on other

00:13:20.560 --> 00:13:22.270
platforms, for example.

00:13:22.270 --> 00:13:25.783
So I'll refer you back
to that for the deep

00:13:25.783 --> 00:13:26.590
dive on this topic.

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:29.950
But essentially, if your app
doesn't conform to the Android

00:13:29.950 --> 00:13:32.340
platform, you're the one who's
going to look out of place.

00:13:32.340 --> 00:13:36.420
If I'm using 50, 60, 70 apps
on my Android phone, and I

00:13:36.420 --> 00:13:38.670
switch to your app, and your app
doesn't look and feel how

00:13:38.670 --> 00:13:41.110
an Android app should look and
feel, then you're the one

00:13:41.110 --> 00:13:42.670
who's going to stand out.

00:13:42.670 --> 00:13:45.670
So some very, very common things
we might see might be,

00:13:45.670 --> 00:13:48.210
for example, using right
pointing carrots to indicate

00:13:48.210 --> 00:13:51.140
that there's a level below
of information.

00:13:51.140 --> 00:13:52.710
That just doesn't make
sense on Android.

00:13:52.710 --> 00:13:54.660
I mean, we have a
very different

00:13:54.660 --> 00:13:57.390
default transition animation.

00:13:57.390 --> 00:14:01.185
So pointing right, and then
something expanding, and

00:14:01.185 --> 00:14:03.880
fading just isn't line up
as well as going back.

00:14:03.880 --> 00:14:04.980
It doesn't slide back
[INAUDIBLE].

00:14:04.980 --> 00:14:07.530
So I guess there's just no
special metaphor there.

00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:10.660
Especially with Android's use of
the horizontal metaphor for

00:14:10.660 --> 00:14:11.770
moving between content.

00:14:11.770 --> 00:14:13.060
So taps, for example.

00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:15.210
You might page between
them like this.

00:14:15.210 --> 00:14:16.700
But then if there's a right
arrow, does that mean I'm

00:14:16.700 --> 00:14:16.970
going down?

00:14:16.970 --> 00:14:17.980
Or I'm going sides?

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:19.410
And every time, it just
doesn't work.

00:14:19.410 --> 00:14:21.480
So respect that.

00:14:21.480 --> 00:14:23.800
Tabs.

00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:25.050
On Android, tabs
go at the top.

00:14:25.050 --> 00:14:28.040
So if you're doing tabs at the
bottom, basically you're going

00:14:28.040 --> 00:14:28.950
to look out of place.

00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:30.240
And it's going to be, why
is this app doing this

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:32.040
differently?

00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:34.810
And the last one we call that
is just wholesale borrowing

00:14:34.810 --> 00:14:36.070
from other platforms.

00:14:36.070 --> 00:14:38.480
This is if you see, say,
iconography from another

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:41.500
platform, or a picker from
another platform, which just

00:14:41.500 --> 00:14:42.920
looks completely out of place.

00:14:42.920 --> 00:14:44.000
Just don't do it.

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:46.570
Just use the defaults, as what
you use is you expect.

00:14:46.570 --> 00:14:48.990
And doing otherwise is being
quite arrogant and aggressive

00:14:48.990 --> 00:14:49.940
toward them.

00:14:49.940 --> 00:14:53.036
So stick with what the
platform [INAUDIBLE].

00:14:53.036 --> 00:14:54.530
ROMAN NURIK: And that
covers it well.

00:14:54.530 --> 00:14:56.860
Let's move on.

00:14:56.860 --> 00:14:58.310
All right.

00:14:58.310 --> 00:14:59.360
Was this me?

00:14:59.360 --> 00:14:59.960
This may have been me.

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:01.770
I think this is me.

00:15:01.770 --> 00:15:04.900
And actually, this plays
into what Nick was

00:15:04.900 --> 00:15:07.390
mentioning about branding.

00:15:07.390 --> 00:15:08.710
Which metaphors do you use?

00:15:08.710 --> 00:15:11.490
Which UI patterns do you use?

00:15:11.490 --> 00:15:14.340
This is the anti-pattern of the
navigation is my brand.

00:15:14.340 --> 00:15:18.370
Or the entire app should
be mine, right?

00:15:18.370 --> 00:15:19.640
I should control everything.

00:15:19.640 --> 00:15:20.630
And generally, that's
the case.

00:15:20.630 --> 00:15:22.760
You should control
visual styling.

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:25.210
You should control the
information architecture.

00:15:25.210 --> 00:15:28.060
And we did a whole
segment on this.

00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:31.690
But there are a few things that
you should really try to

00:15:31.690 --> 00:15:33.870
use from the Android
design guidelines.

00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:36.150
Obviously, Pure Android,
that's very important.

00:15:36.150 --> 00:15:39.230
But also, anything related
to core app navigation.

00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:41.180
So things like the action bar.

00:15:41.180 --> 00:15:42.660
Things like tabs.

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:44.500
And also things like
the navigation jar.

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:49.360
So this anti-pattern is
basically apps that reinvent

00:15:49.360 --> 00:15:51.910
the wheel, by creating
a custom top bar

00:15:51.910 --> 00:15:53.940
with a centered title.

00:15:53.940 --> 00:15:56.480
And then two actions, one on
the left, one on the right.

00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:58.550
They're like a very
different looking

00:15:58.550 --> 00:16:00.900
navigation jar indicator.

00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:02.950
This basically isn't
Android, right?

00:16:02.950 --> 00:16:06.690
I mean, Android users expect
an action bar the top.

00:16:06.690 --> 00:16:07.910
The title should be
left aligned.

00:16:07.910 --> 00:16:10.600
There are certain things
that should existent

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:11.690
in the action bar.

00:16:11.690 --> 00:16:15.980
Navigation on the top left,
actions on the top right.

00:16:15.980 --> 00:16:18.430
Or very poorly implemented
action bars.

00:16:18.430 --> 00:16:24.360
And generally, this is because
of the lack of the tool kit

00:16:24.360 --> 00:16:26.300
that allow you to bring the
action bar to earlier versions

00:16:26.300 --> 00:16:27.980
of the platform.

00:16:27.980 --> 00:16:31.490
But Action Bar Sherlock has
existed for quite a while.

00:16:31.490 --> 00:16:34.250
And that's still
a great choice.

00:16:34.250 --> 00:16:36.590
But also Action Bar Compat
was recently released.

00:16:36.590 --> 00:16:39.140
So for designers and
developers--

00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:40.540
well, for developers
especially--

00:16:40.540 --> 00:16:44.070
if you're rolling your own
action bar, just stop.

00:16:44.070 --> 00:16:44.630
Stop doing it.

00:16:44.630 --> 00:16:46.680
And just use Action
Bar Compat.

00:16:46.680 --> 00:16:48.990
But also, navigation drawers.

00:16:48.990 --> 00:16:50.790
I'm not going to go through
all the details here.

00:16:50.790 --> 00:16:53.795
But there are a lot of specifics
in what should and

00:16:53.795 --> 00:16:56.970
what shouldn't go into
navigation drawer.

00:16:56.970 --> 00:16:59.620
Generally, anything that's not
really core app navigation.

00:16:59.620 --> 00:17:01.660
Something that the user's going
to be switching between

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:03.510
someone often.

00:17:03.510 --> 00:17:05.819
That probably shouldn't go
to navigation drawer.

00:17:05.819 --> 00:17:08.359
And we did another full episode
on this, so I won't go

00:17:08.359 --> 00:17:09.410
into the details.

00:17:09.410 --> 00:17:11.339
But if you're a developer, you
should definitely be using

00:17:11.339 --> 00:17:14.369
Drawer Layout and Action
Bar Drawer toggle.

00:17:14.369 --> 00:17:17.859
Try to avoid using any of the
other libraries out there that

00:17:17.859 --> 00:17:19.560
don't implement this way.

00:17:19.560 --> 00:17:22.430
Because you're not going to get
the same interaction that

00:17:22.430 --> 00:17:23.680
the platform provides.

00:17:26.460 --> 00:17:28.260
And in this vantage, I want to
quickly point out some things

00:17:28.260 --> 00:17:30.990
that shouldn't go in the
navigation drawer.

00:17:30.990 --> 00:17:33.290
So Home, Explore, Shop
Now, My Profile.

00:17:33.290 --> 00:17:36.340
That's fine, and that's kind of
core top level navigation.

00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:37.500
Things like search--

00:17:37.500 --> 00:17:40.570
its navigational, but by
platform convention, it should

00:17:40.570 --> 00:17:42.160
really go into the action bar.

00:17:42.160 --> 00:17:43.580
So it does not belong here.

00:17:43.580 --> 00:17:46.180
Settings, also in the
action overflow.

00:17:46.180 --> 00:17:49.220
Help, About, Send Feedback, that
should all go into the

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:50.570
action overflow.

00:17:50.570 --> 00:17:54.120
Anything linking to other apps
that your brand offers, that

00:17:54.120 --> 00:17:55.790
should probably not go here.

00:17:55.790 --> 00:17:58.590
Because chances are, folks don't
care about every app in

00:17:58.590 --> 00:17:59.870
your portfolio.

00:17:59.870 --> 00:18:02.090
So generally, you want to put
that-- if you do want to place

00:18:02.090 --> 00:18:05.390
it in your app, put that
somewhere deeper in the app.

00:18:05.390 --> 00:18:10.230
Maybe about your brand, and in
there, list the other things.

00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:11.700
And then obviously,
random things that

00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:12.520
people will never click.

00:18:12.520 --> 00:18:14.380
Like my sister's friends'
website that I promise is

00:18:14.380 --> 00:18:14.870
really awesome.

00:18:14.870 --> 00:18:15.810
Please check it out.

00:18:15.810 --> 00:18:17.990
That does not belong in
the navigation drawer.

00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:19.560
So try to keep it simple.

00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:22.960
Try to keep it to what's
in the guidelines.

00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:25.230
Let's move on.

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:26.190
NICK BUTCHER: All right.

