But there's a lot of them.

00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:45.920
And we see it a lot.

00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:47.300
But I didn't want to
sort of ding any

00:18:47.300 --> 00:18:48.480
particular app out there.

00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:50.120
So put in some positive
examples.

00:18:50.120 --> 00:18:52.030
Positive reinforcement is the
name of the game here.

00:18:54.790 --> 00:18:59.850
So Android has a great ability
to share or use this action

00:18:59.850 --> 00:19:02.470
sending tent between
applications.

00:19:02.470 --> 00:19:03.600
So you should always use it.

00:19:03.600 --> 00:19:05.590
Always make it available
to your users.

00:19:05.590 --> 00:19:08.720
Again, along the same
things that we were

00:19:08.720 --> 00:19:09.550
talking about before.

00:19:09.550 --> 00:19:11.870
It's just a frustrating
experience when the user goes

00:19:11.870 --> 00:19:15.430
to try and share something, and
they're stuck with one or

00:19:15.430 --> 00:19:17.840
two static options.

00:19:17.840 --> 00:19:20.060
As you can see here, on my
phone, I have tons of

00:19:20.060 --> 00:19:21.230
different apps installed.

00:19:21.230 --> 00:19:23.360
I share to different
apps all the time.

00:19:23.360 --> 00:19:26.140
And so not having the ability
to choose the one that you

00:19:26.140 --> 00:19:28.290
want to share to is just a
really frustrating user

00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:29.510
experience.

00:19:29.510 --> 00:19:31.930
Just to quickly go over
the examples here.

00:19:31.930 --> 00:19:34.840
On the left, you've got the
share action provider.

00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:37.680
And so that's something that
goes directly in the action

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:41.060
bar, and actually has a pop up
menu that drops down there.

00:19:41.060 --> 00:19:43.440
And you can choose from your
most recently, or most

00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:47.100
frequently, shared
applications.

00:19:47.100 --> 00:19:49.720
And then, the second one is
the standard system share

00:19:49.720 --> 00:19:51.280
dialogue that you can
trigger using that

00:19:51.280 --> 00:19:53.490
action sending tent.

00:19:53.490 --> 00:19:56.230
And then on the right, this is
a custom example, actually,

00:19:56.230 --> 00:19:58.750
from the Timely app, which
I really like.

00:19:58.750 --> 00:20:01.870
So in this case, they actually
have listed just a few to

00:20:01.870 --> 00:20:02.745
start with.

00:20:02.745 --> 00:20:04.870
But you can see that they have
this little drop-down at the

00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:07.110
bottom saying "more", which
actually goes and

00:20:07.110 --> 00:20:09.180
pragmatically fetches
the rest of the

00:20:09.180 --> 00:20:10.640
sharing options available.

00:20:10.640 --> 00:20:13.620
So I guess the moral of the
story is try and always use

00:20:13.620 --> 00:20:15.420
the system sharing tents.

00:20:15.420 --> 00:20:19.430
If you really must for some
reason, have a list of

00:20:19.430 --> 00:20:20.860
specific networks.

00:20:20.860 --> 00:20:22.350
Maybe it's part of your
business goals

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:23.740
or something else.

00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:26.730
You should still compliment it
with the standard action

00:20:26.730 --> 00:20:27.980
[? send ?] based sharing
alongside.

00:20:30.760 --> 00:20:32.650
ROMAN NURIK: OK.

00:20:32.650 --> 00:20:33.700
Actually, one more thing.

00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:35.890
This actually is in the Pure
Android guidelines, right?

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:40.300
So again, don't violate any of
the pure Android guidelines.

00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:42.110
Try to adhere to those
as best as possible.

00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:42.740
And this is--

00:20:42.740 --> 00:20:44.778
I think it's called-- don't
hard code links to

00:20:44.778 --> 00:20:45.920
apps in your app.

00:20:45.920 --> 00:20:46.720
ADAM KOCH: And actually--

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.160
sorry, one last thing--

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:51.180
from a development standpoint,
it's actually much easier to

00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:53.000
use the system sharing
tents than going off

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:54.500
and do it all yourself.

00:20:54.500 --> 00:20:57.370
So I mean, from a development
standpoint, it's also a

00:20:57.370 --> 00:20:59.202
positive thing.

00:20:59.202 --> 00:20:59.700
ROMAN NURIK: Absolutely.

